title: LS ethics panel hears Dubey, Dehadrai; calls Mahua Oct 31
description: The ethics committee of Parliament has summoned Trinamool Congress MP Mahua Moitra to record her statement in response to allegations of "cash for query" made by BJP MP Nishikant Dubey and advocate Jai Anant Dehadrai. The committee has also requested assistance from the ministries of home affairs and IT to provide details about the conversation between Moitra, Dehadrai, and businessman Darshan Hiranandani. Dubey expressed confidence and stated that the proceedings were focused on Moitra's conduct. The committee is chaired by BJP MP Vinod Kumar Sonkar and includes members from various political parties.

title: Scientists crack reasons behind resilience of dengue-spreaders
description: Researchers from IIT Mandi and inStem Bengaluru have discovered the molecular reasons behind the ability of Aedes Aegypti mosquito eggs to survive without water for long periods. The study found that the eggs enter an altered metabolic state, increasing the production of polyamines, which help them withstand water loss. The eggs also use high-calorie lipids as an energy source after rehydration. Understanding these survival mechanisms could lead to innovative mosquito control strategies and potentially help in finding solutions for agricultural challenges.

title: 2 families, continents apart, bond over Xmas cake and memories
description: A family from Suffolk, England, has a unique connection to a bakery in Kannur, Kerala. The Brown family's ancestors ran a cinnamon plantation in Kannur in the 1800s and had a special Christmas cake made by a local bakery. The cake, known as the 'Brown Family Cinnamon Christmas Cake', was made with local ingredients and a cashew and banana brew instead of French brandy. The Brown family recently visited the bakery and presented them with a cake made by a French pastry chef as a tribute to their shared history.

title: In a first, blind student makes it to IIIT-Lucknow
description: A visually impaired student has been admitted to the Indian Institute of Information Technology in Lucknow. Bhuvika Agrawal, a 19-year-old BTech student from Mumbai, overcame her disability to excel in coding and secure a place at one of the country's top engineering institutes. With a 100% blindness, Bhuvika used technology and her own hard work to crack the JEE (Mains) exam. She visualized diagrams and solved problems by dictating her answers to a scribe. The IIIT-L director commended her determination to study like a normal student without additional support.

title: Para Asiad: Ex-banker bags two golds, mason's daughter wins silver
description: Two differently abled athletes from western Uttar Pradesh have achieved success at the Asian Para Games 2023 in Hangzhou, China. Ankur Dhama, who is visually impaired, won two gold medals in the 5,000m and 1,500m events. Zainab Khatoon, who is paralysed below the waist, won a silver medal in women's 61kg powerlifting. Ankur lost his vision at the age of seven due to an infection, while Zainab was partially paralysed at the age of six. Both athletes overcame their challenges through hard work and determination.

title: Man sexually abuses dog, throws it from 3rd floor
description: "In response to the neighbor's outcry, the accused tossed the female dog onto the street from the balcony, resulting in injuries to the animal. Following the filing of an FIR in the case, the accused was apprehended this evening," PTI quoted Vinod Kumar Mishra, who serves as the in-charge of the local Beta 2 police station, as saying.

title: Kohli bowls to Gill in nets ahead of England match
description: Virat Kohli has been in outstanding form in the ODI World Cup, but the star Indian batter isn't limiting himself to just his batting prowess as he was seen honing his bowling skills during the net session on Thursday.

title: Domestic help robs producer of Rs 10.35L via app
description: On Tuesday, Ramesh Jagdish Sharma, a 65-year-old film producer known for his works in movies such as "Baaghi," "Ek Tha Raja," "Aakrosh," "Pyaasa," and "Game," all of which were released in the 1990s, lodged a complaint with the DN Nagar police station, as confirmed by the official.

title: "England underestimated Sri Lanka": Maheesh Theekshana
description: Sri Lankan spinner Maheesh Theekshana didn't mince words and said that the defending champions England had underestimated the Islanders at their own risk. Sri Lanka cruised to an eight-wicket defeat against the 2019 champions England and dented their hopes of reaching the semifinals of the mega tournament. The Sri Lankan bowlers demonstrated remarkable accuracy on a pitch with unpredictable bounce, dismantling England's lineup for a mere 156 runs.

title: Maratha quota: Trio who attacked advocate's car felicitated
description: During this, the main accused Mangesh Sable said that the Maharashtra government should give a long-lasting Maratha reservation as soon as possible otherwise "the situation will go out of hand".

title: Students branded with hot steel spoon in Gujarat
description: The administrator of an unregistered residential school in Gujarat's Sabarkantha district has been accused of branding at least 12 minor students with a hot steel spoon as a form of punishment.

title: 'Don't undertake Viksit Bharat Sankalp Yatra in poll-bound states'
description: The Election Commission has requested the central government to postpone the proposed Viksit Bharat Sankalp Yatra in poll-bound states until December 5. The yatra was planned to reach out to beneficiaries of social welfare schemes and enroll those who have not yet received the benefits. The campaign includes mobile performing vans, mobile theatre vans, and the use of drones in farming.

title: EC issues notice to Priyanka Gandhi over remarks on PM Modi
Now, premature withdrawal allowed on fixed deposits up to Rs 1 crore
description: Non-callable FDs are term deposits that do not permit premature withdrawals until the tenure is completed. Once you invest in these FDs, your funds remain locked until the FD matures.

title: EC issues notice to Assam CM for 'Akbar' remarks
description: During his speech in Kawardha in Chhattisgarh on October 18, Sarma had taken a controversial dig at Akbar saying that "the land of Mata Kaushalya will get defiled if Akbar isn't sent off."

title: Sri Lanka push England closer to World Cup exit
description: Sri Lanka dealt a severe blow to England's hopes of advancing in the WC, delivering an emphatic 8-wicket win that brought the defending champions to the brink of elimination.

title: Delhi's air quality remains poor, any respite unlikely soon
description: At 4 pm, the city's 24-hour average Air Quality Index (AQI) was recorded at 256, showing a deterioration from 243 on Wednesday and 220 on Tuesday.

title: India may send more weapons to Armenia amid Azerbaijan tensions
description: India is contemplating additional military aid for Armenia, its strategic ally in the Caucasus, the Economic Times has reported. According to the report, India is planning to send additional shipment which may include military equipment aimed at enhancing Armenia's deterrence capabilities. This comes amid Armenia's conflict-like situation with Azerbaijan, which is backed by Pakistan and Turkey. The decision comes after the successful delivery of an initial batch of weaponry last year, the ET report said.

title: Israel taps Pegasus spyware maker to track hostages in Gaza Strip
description: Israel is reportedly enlisting the help of spyware companies, including NSO Group and Candiru, to track hostages in the Gaza Strip. The companies are being asked to upgrade their spyware capabilities to meet the needs of Israel's security forces. Several software firms, including Rayzone and Paragon, are collaborating on the requests and offering their services for free. The involvement of NSO Group and Candiru has raised concerns due to their controversial track records.

title: Journalist murder: Hearing on sentencing on Nov 7
description: On October 18, additional sessions judge (ASJ) Ravindra Kumar Pandey rendered guilty verdicts for Ravi Kapoor, Amit Shukla, Baljeet Malik, and Ajay Kumar under IPC section 302 (murder) and the provisions of the Maharashtra Control of Organised Crime Act (MCOCA).

title: Indian youth should work 70 hrs a week: Infy's Murthy
description: In conversation with former Infosys CFO Mohandas Pai, Narayana Murthy stressed on the need to pick the right habits from the West. “Somehow our youth have the habit of taking not so desirable habits from the west and then not helping the country,” he said.

title: Rape of minor girls: NHRC seeks report from Mayurbhanj SP
description: The National Human Rights Commission (NHRC) has sought action taken report from Mayurbhanj SP in two different cases related to sexual assault of two minor girls by cops of a police station in Mayurbhanj district.

title: In a first, India, EU carry out joint naval drills in Gulf of Guinea
description: India and the European Union conducted their first joint naval exercise in the Gulf of Guinea, reflecting their growing maritime security cooperation. The exercise aimed to reinforce naval maritime security cooperation and uphold the United Nations Convention on Law of the Sea. Ships from the Indian Navy and three EU member states participated in tactical manoeuvres, boarding exercises, and knowledge sharing sessions. The exercise demonstrated the shared commitment of India and the EU to ensuring maritime security in the Gulf of Guinea.

title: Who are the 8 Indian Navy veterans sentenced to death in Qatar
Gavaskar makes huge prediction on Kohli's 50th ODI ton
description: Virat Kohli may have fallen short of his 49th ODI century, but legendary Sunil Gavaskar is confident that the former skipper's 50th hundred is in sight and believes that Kohli will achieve this milestone on his birthday, which falls on November 5. On that day, India will face South Africa in their second-to-last group match at Eden Gardens. Kohli came close to equalling Sachin Tendulkar's record for most ODI hundreds (49) but got dismissed for 95 against New Zealand before India chased down its target of 274.

title: 5 American cars Indians love despite US carmakers’ failure to woo the market
description: The last car on the list is also the only one still on sale in India, it is not only the Wrangler but the Jeep brand itself has been fairly successful in the Indian market and currently has a portfolio of four SUVs from the compact SUV to the high-end segment. Jeep also has long-term plans to stay in India.

title: Infiltration bid foiled in J&K's Kupwara, five terrorists killed
description: Five terrorists were killed in an encounter between terrorists and security personnel in Jammu and Kashmir's Kupwara district in the Machhal sector on Thursday. Earlier in the day, in a joint operation with Jammu and Kashmir Police, personnel of the Indian Army foiled an infiltration bid along the Line of Control in the Kupwara sector.

title: 'Morphed video': Punjab police arrest SAD leader Bunty Romana
description: Romana had allegedly posted a "forged and morphed video" of Punjabi singer Kanwar Grewal on X platform to harm the reputation of Punjab chief minister Bhagwant Mann for political mileage.

title: China's videos shows ‘provocative’ actions by US ship
description: China's military has released video footage accusing a US warship of "provocative" actions in the South China Sea. The video shows the USS Ralph Johnson allegedly conducting close-in harassment against a Chinese navy task group. China claims that the US warship made sharp turns, crossed the bow of a Chinese ship, and dangerously approached Chinese navy vessels. The Chinese Defense Ministry has labeled the US as the "real provoker" and threatened to take necessary measures to safeguard national sovereignty.

title: 'I took 40 balls to get off the mark': Gavaskar hails Maxwell
description: As Glenn Maxwell smoked the fastest-ever ODI World Cup century on Wednesday against Netherlands -- off just 40 balls -- legendary Sunil Gavaskar was in all praise of the swashbuckling all-rounder. The 35-year-old was in carnage mode against Dutch in the national capital as he hammered 9 fours and 8 sixes on his way to a mind-boggling 44-ball 106.

title: Mumbai: Discharge plea of Uddhav, Raut rejected
description: A magistrate’s court in Mumbai on Thursday rejected the discharge plea filed by Shiv Sena (UBT) chief Uddhav Thackeray and MP Sanjay Raut in the defamation case filed by MP Rahul Shewale.

title: Greg Chappell facing financial woes; fundraising campaign started
description: Cricket icon Greg Chappell has disclosed that he's been facing financial challenges, and his friends have come together to establish an online fundraising platform aimed at "improving his quality of life in his later years," as reported.

title: 8 Indians awarded death penalty in Qatar; deeply shocked by verdict, says MEA
'Swiss woman killer lured women with gemstones'
description: The police officer mentioned that they have successfully retrieved Gurpreet Singh's conversations with various other foreign women from his two mobile phones.

title: 'The only thing Babar Azam can do is...': Wasim Akram
description: There has been a growing demand to replace Babar Azam as the captain of the Pakistan cricket team following the shock loss to Afghanistan, which has left their ODI World Cup campaign in tatters. Former Pakistan players including legendary Wasim Akram launched an all out attack on the players for their poor fitness and lacklustre performances. But he now has offered his support saying we as a nation should do our bit to boost the morale of our players.

title: 5 useless car accessories that Indians love!
description: Modern cars have sensors for various safety features such as ADAS, parking aid and mainly for airbags and these safety features can be disabled or can cause it to malfunction. Installing bullbars are also illegal in India and can attract hefty fines.

title: BMW iX1 'Gone in 180 minutes': 1,000+ EVs delivered in India
description: Responding to the query about the body-style split presently, Pawah told us that SUVs account for 56% of total sales currently and the split between petrol and diesel is balanced with a slight inclination towards petrol. In addition, EVs already account for about 10% of total sales, proving the potential for the future, added Pawah.

title: ED raids: BJP playing dirty game, says Mamata
description: “The BJP is playing a dirty game. I want to ask whether there has been a single ED raid at any BJP leader's residence. BJP says it wants 'Sabka Sath Sabka Vikas', but it actually means 'Sabka Sath Sabka Satyanash’,” Mamata said referring to the ED raids on opposition leaders across the country ahead of elections.

title: Cash-for-query row: LS panel calls Mahua on Oc 31
description: The Lok Sabha Ethics Committee has summoned TMC MP Mahua Moitra on October 31 regarding the cash-for-query allegations against her. The committee plans to seek assistance from the home and IT ministries in their investigation. Earlier, lawyer Jai Anant Dehadrai and BJP leader Nishikant Dubey provided their statements to the Ethics Committee. BJP member Nishikant Dubey had filed a complaint, alleging that Mahua Moitra accepted bribes to target the Adani Group and Prime Minister Narendra Modi. Moitra has denied these allegations and accused the Adani Group of being behind the charges.

title: 'Understand the individual...': Rohit discloses his management strategy
description: Captain Rohit Sharma discussed his management strategy for India's squad during the 2023 Men's ODI World Cup. Under his leadership, Team India has won all its league matches so far and he has been delivering electrifying starts. As the team prepares to face defending champions England on October 29, Rohit emphasized the importance of understanding each player as an individual and catering to their specific needs.

description: Big Hit Music has issued a strong statement denying the involvement of BTS' in the latest celebrity drug controversy, which has rocked the Korean entertainment industry. Fans of the Bangtan boys have also reacted strongly to the rumours. Read on to know more about the controversy.

title: Guesthouse owner shot for refusing extortion
description: The owner, Jameel Ahmed Abdul Kareem (51), slumped in his chair with a bullet lodged in his skull and was stabbed twice by the accused to ensure his death.

title: Babar's captaincy in jeopardy as PCB hints at potential change
description: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) is considering the removal of skipper Babar Azam if the team's performance in the World Cup continues to decline. Pakistan are currently in a must-win situation against South Africa in Chennai, with a loss in this crucial match potentially eliminating their chances of advancing to the semifinals. Pressure is mounting on Azam and the team to salvage their World Cup campaign with a victory.

title: Gang dismantles ATM, robs Rs 32L; sets it ablaze
description: But the free run of the gang was cut short after Madhya Pradesh police nabbed the goons in Indore and alerted their Nagpur counterparts on Wednesday.

title: Pakistan issues last warning to illegal refugees
description: Pakistan is increasing its efforts to deport all illegal immigrants, including around 1.7 million Afghans. The country is establishing deportation centers and has set a deadline of November 1 for all undocumented migrants to leave voluntarily. Those who do not comply will be arrested and sent to the deportation centers. The decision primarily impacts Afghan refugees who sought shelter in Pakistan during times of turmoil. The move comes after Afghan nationals were found to be involved in crimes and attacks against the government and army.

title: How to play Indian markets ahead of Diwali Muhurat trading
description: Traders looking to profit from the stock market ahead of Diwali should consider investing in the Nifty and specific sectors such as auto and consumer discretionary. According to a study by Samco Securities, the Nifty has shown positive gains in nine out of ten occasions during the period between Navaratri and Diwali's Muhurat Trading Day over the past decade.

title: BMW X4 M40i launched in India at Rs 96.2 lakh
description: BMW claims the SUV can sprint from 0-100 km/hr in just 4.9 seconds and has a top speed of 250 km/hr. The engine also gets 48-volt mild hybrid technology. The car also gets different driving modes such as ECO PRO, COMFORT, SPORT and SPORT Plus.

title: WC: Babar's captaincy at stake as Pakistan face SA
description: Babar Azam's captaincy is in jeopardy as Pakistan face South Africa in a crucial World Cup match. A fourth loss could seal Pakistan's exit from the tournament and potentially end Babar Azam's captaincy. Pakistan must secure victories in all remaining matches and hope Australia fail in at least two of their games to maintain their semi-final hopes. The unpredictable nature of the Pakistan cricket team is a common feature of world cricket.

title: PM Modi offers prayers at Shirdi temple, to launch projects
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi visited the Shirdi temple in Maharashtra and inaugurated the new 'darshan queue complex'. He also launched a scheme to benefit over 86 lakh farmers and unveiled multiple development projects worth approximately Rs 7,500 crore. Later, he traveled to Goa to inaugurate the 37th National Games, where he addressed the participating athletes. The Games will take place from October 26 to November 9, with over 10,000 athletes competing in various sports disciplines.

title: Watch: What doctor found in a women's ear, will shock you
description: A 64-year-old woman visited the doctor complaining of strange sounds in her left ear. Upon examination, doctors discovered a small spider and its exoskeleton inside her ear canal. The woman had been unable to sleep due to the movement of the spider, which caused rustling and ticking sounds. Doctors used a tube to remove the spider and its exoskeleton.

title: 4 ways US proposes to change H-1B visa programme
description: The US Department of Homeland Security (DHS) has proposed changes to the H-1B visa program to streamline eligibility requirements, improve efficiency, and provide greater benefits. The proposed rule aims to clarify specialty occupation positions, defer to previous determinations, expand exemptions for certain organizations, extend flexibilities for students, establish eligibility requirements for entrepreneurs, and strengthen integrity measures. Additionally, the proposed changes would modify the H-1B registration selection process to reduce misuse and fraud by only allowing one registration per individual, improving the chances for legitimate registrations to be selected.

title: Koffee with Karan 8: Ranveer, Deepika bash separation rumours
description: The debut episode of Koffee With Karan Season 8 featured Ranveer Singh and Deepika Padukone, who addressed divorce rumors and expressed their love for each other. They discussed their 11-year relationship, marriage, and Deepika's battle with depression. Ranveer dominated the conversation, leaving host Karan Johar speechless at times. The episode ended with a romantic atmosphere and inspired singles looking for love.

title: Mysterious sackings of top ministers in China: Is Xi facing a challenge to his authority?
description: China has removed two high-profile ministers, defense minister Li Shangfu and foreign minister Qin Gang, both handpicked by President Xi Jinping, without any official explanation. The sackings have raised questions about Xi's authority and political ambitions. Some analysts suggest that the ministers may have violated Xi's demand for loyalty or posed a threat to his power. Xi has been consolidating control over the military, security apparatus, and economic policy, but he also faces challenges such as slowing economic growth and international pressure.

title: 5 big traffic challans that can hurt your pocket badly
description: Data shows that traffic violations are ever increasing and from not having a valid PUC certificate to over 1,300 deaths due to driving under the influence (DUI) in 2021 alone, Indian drivers are casually breaking traffic rules and putting everyone at risk. Here are five big traffic violations that the government has made expensive in its bid to make Indian roads safer.

title: Wedding bells for actress Amala Paul soon
description: Actress Amala Paul, has accepted her friend Jagat Desai's proposal for marriage and the two are expected to get married soon.

title: Certified polished diamond prices drop by 35% to 2004 level
description: Certified polished diamonds prices have dropped significantly, falling by 35% during Dussehra when compared to last year's Navratri-Dussehra period. The decrease in diamond prices has resulted in a 20% increase in sales across stores in India. The maximum price drop has occurred in diamonds ranging from 0.25 carats to 3 carats.

title: 6-month pregnant woman 'beaten to death' by in-laws
description: A pregnant woman in Biharsharif was allegedly beaten to death by her in-laws after they discovered through an illegal ultrasound that she was carrying a girl child. The victim, Kusum Devi, was six months pregnant and already had two daughters and a visually impaired son. Her husband and in-laws have gone into hiding. The police have dismissed the family's claim regarding the ultrasound and are investigating the case based on the complaint and postmortem report. The deceased's sister has accused the husband and his relatives of murder.

title: Google is making more money than it did in the last 12 months
description: Alphabet, the parent company of Google, has reported strong third-quarter earnings, beating analyst expectations. The company's revenue grew by 11% to $76.6 billion, while net income increased by 46% to $19.7 billion. The growth was driven by Search and YouTube advertising, as well as the Google Cloud business which saw a 40% increase in revenue. Alphabet's CEO, Sundar Pichai, emphasized the company's focus on making AI more helpful for everyone.

title: FEMA case: ED summons Rajasthan CM Ashok Gehlot's son
Double tap on Apple Watch: How Apple implemented its 'coolest' feature of 2023
description: Apple has introduced a new double tap gesture for its Watch Series 9 and Watch Ultra 2 models. The feature allows users to perform common actions by tapping their index finger and thumb together twice. While the gesture looks cool, there is some skepticism about its reliability. Apple claims to have ensured that the gesture is triggered accurately by using an algorithm that detects wrist movements and changes in blood flow. However, the double tap feature is currently limited and does not work underwater or in certain apps and features.

title: Pakistan may bank on finger spin to counter South Africa
description: Pakistan face a tough challenge against South Africa in the World Cup. South Africa are on the verge of reaching the semifinals with four wins, while Pakistan need to win against them to stay in the competition. Quinton de Kock's impressive performance in the tournament poses a threat to Pakistan, but they can target him with finger spinners. Pakistan's Shadab Khan has been practicing finger spin, and left-arm spinner Mohammad Nawaz may also be included in the team.

title: 'Everything sort of clicked...': Smith reveals how he returned to form
description: Australian cricketer Steve Smith has attributed his return to form in the World Cup to technical adjustments. Smith displayed his revamped technique in a 68-ball 71 against the Netherlands, combining with David Warner for 132 runs. He revealed that he had worked on a couple of things during net sessions on Tuesday, moving back to the leg stump and getting his hands higher. This helped him feel more comfortable in the nets and regain his form after Australia's 309-run victory over the Netherlands.

title: ‘Little Gaza’: How Israeli troops are training for a ground assault on Hamas
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has announced that Israel is proceeding with plans for a ground assault in the Gaza Strip, with the timing to be determined by the war cabinet and the military. The ongoing Israeli aerial attacks have resulted in numerous casualties, and global leaders, including US President Joe Biden, have urged Israel to protect innocent lives and comply with wartime laws.

title: How cloud seeding led to 18% more rainfall here
description: A recent study published in the Bulletin of the American Meteorological Society (BAMS) reveals that a cloud seeding experiment conducted in the Solapur region of Maharashtra resulted in 18% more rainfall than normal conditions. The experiment involved hygroscopic cloud seeding, which triggered rainfall in convective clouds. The study also evaluated glaciogenic seeding in cold clouds but found no significant impact on rainfall at the seeding location. However, an increase in rainfall was observed in the downwind area of the seeded region. Scientists recommend the use of hygroscopic cloud seeding to enhance rainfall in water-scarce regions.

title: Comedian Anubhav buys Range Rover Sport: What's special about it?
description: Range Rover claims that the range-topping Sport SV Edition One with the 4.4-litre turbo-petrol engine can sprint from 0 to 100 km/h in just 3.8 seconds.

title: Apple rolls out iOS 17.1 with new features
description: Apple has released the iOS 17.1 update for iPhones, offering new features such as the ability to AirDrop files over the internet, expanded favorites in Apple Music, and new options for controlling the display's standby mode. The update also includes fixes for security vulnerabilities, battery life issues, performance problems, and app crashes. Users are encouraged to update their devices to iOS 17.1 to access these new features and enhance security. The update is available for all iPhones that can run iOS 17, including iPhone XR and later models.

title: Here’s how to protect seniors citizen from financial frauds
description: Elderly individuals are often targeted by scammers due to their limited familiarity with technology. Fraudsters use tactics such as fake insurance schemes, low-cost medications, and fake social media accounts to trick seniors into sharing personal and financial information. To protect themselves, seniors should be aware of fraudsters pretending to be from banks or other institutions, avoid sharing sensitive information over the phone or internet, and enable multi-factor authentication for their accounts. It is important to remember that banks and financial institutions will never ask for sensitive information.

title: How well is Virat Kohli placed to play the LA 2028 Olympics
description: India has made a significant move in hosting the 2036 Olympic Games, thanks to Prime Minister Narendra Modi's acknowledgement of the country's efforts. Cricket has also returned to the biggest stage of multi-sport events after a wait of 128 years. The 141st IOC Session in Mumbai marked the return of cricket to the Los Angeles 2028 Olympic programme. Kohli is the name most synonymous with cricket even in regions where it is either not played or has started to make its presence felt.

title: Sensex & Nifty in free fall! Investors lose Rs 3.5L cr in 15 mins
description: Sensex & Nifty continue to slide: Benchmark equity indices continued their downward trend for the sixth consecutive session on Thursday, mirroring the global market sentiment impacted by concerns over US Treasury yields, the ongoing Middle East conflict and Tech Mahindra's underwhelming earnings report. The BSE Sensex witnessed a decline of 600 points, falling below the 63,500 mark

title: Maine mass shooting: What we know about the shooter
description: A mass shooting in Lewiston, Maine has left 22 people dead. The suspect, identified as Robert Card, is a trained firearms instructor associated with the Army Reserve. Card had previously mentioned hearing voices and had threatened a shooting at the National Guard Base where he was stationed. He had also been admitted to a mental health facility during the summer. Authorities have released a photograph of a white Subaru Outback that they believe might be connected to the suspect.

title: IAF officer's wife dies in freak accident on Yamuna e-way
description: A woman died and three others were seriously injured in a road accident on the Yamuna expressway in Mathura district. The wife of an Indian Air Force officer was thrown from the expressway and died on the spot, while her children escaped with minor injuries. The accident occurred when a speeding car collided with their vehicle from behind. The injured passengers were rushed to the hospital for treatment. The Yamuna expressway has seen a total of 7,256 accidents, resulting in 1,242 deaths and 10,520 injuries, over the past 12 years.

title: 12 killed after car rams truck on NH-44 in Karnataka
description: At least 12 people were killed after the car they were travelling rammed into a stationary truck on National Highway 44 in Karnataka's Chikkaballapur on Thursday morning. The deceased belonged to Gorantla area of Andhra Pradesh's Sri Sathya Sai district.

title: Farmers in UP taking crop loans to buy luxury cars?
Businessman fires in air as delivery person arrives late with pizza
description: A quarrel over a late pizza delivery led to the son of a stone crushing unit owner in Pune firing a round in the air with his licensed pistol. The incident occurred in a residential area, but no one was injured. The police have registered a case against the son, Chetan Vasant Padwal, for attempt to commit culpable homicide, assault, intentional insult, and criminal intimidation. Padwal had placed the pizza delivery order online and got into an argument with the delivery person for arriving late.

title: 'JD(U) dubbed Nitish as suicide bomber, it’s strange'
description: The BJP and JD(U) have engaged in a political slugfest in Bihar after BJP state president Samrat Choudhary posted an animation on social media, depicting RJD chief Lalu Prasad as Ravana, his son Tejashwi Yadav as Meghnad, and CM Nitish Kumar as Kumbhakaran. JD(U) spokesperson Neeraj Kumar responded by calling Nitish Kumar a "time bomb" that would disrupt the BJP's 2024 plans. The BJP retaliated by calling Nitish Kumar a "suicide bomber." The controversy has escalated, with both parties defending their statements. Meanwhile, the JD(U) has decided to field candidates in Madhya Pradesh, indicating possible cracks in the opposition alliance.

title: Boys, 13 & 14, confess to killing 'bossy' friend
description: Two boys, aged 13 and 14, have been taken into custody in Amethi for the murder of their 14-year-old friend. The victim had been acting like a boss, taking their money and humiliating them. In order to get rid of him, the two boys invited him to a party and served him a drugged drink. They then slit his throat and fled. The boys have confessed to the crime and have been sent to a shelter home.

title: 'There is no way...': Akhtar makes bold prediction about India's chances
description: Team India has dominated the ODI World Cup so far with five consecutive victories, including notable victories against Australia, Pakistan, and New Zealand. Former Pakistani cricket legend Shoaib Akhtar believes that even without key players, Shubman Gill, KL Rahul, and Rohit Sharma can outclass the Kiwis. Virat Kohli emerged as a hero in India's chase, scoring a commendable 95 to lead his team to victory. Akhtar praised Kohli's ability to thrive under pressure, stating that pressure brings opportunities for him.

title: T'gana: Cong goes to town with BRS & BJP ‘wedding card’
World Cup: Hardik Pandya has ligament tear, likely to miss more games
description: Hardik Pandya's participation in the remaining World Cup matches is in jeopardy due to a suspected Grade 1 ligament tear in his ankle. The Indian team management is reworking their plan and is against rushing him back into the squad. His availability for the next few matches is doubtful, and a decision on his involvement will be taken next week. TOI understands that the Indian team is against rushing him back into the squad. Hardik's body has been prone to injuries all through his career. This has left Hardik very disappointed and worried, it was learnt.

title: PM Modi to inaugurate slew of projects in Shirdi today
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi is set to inaugurate various development projects in Shirdi, including the temple Darshan Queue Complex and the left bank canal network. He will also launch the Namo Shetkari Mahasanman Nidhi Yojana and distribute Ayushman and Svamitva cards. Additionally, PM Modi will inaugurate projects such as the Ayush hospital, electrification of railway sections, and four-laning of road sections. Animal welfare activists are urging authorities to protect stray dogs in Shirdi during the PM's visit.

title: Woman walking to office run over by SUV on NH-8
description: A 30-year-old woman died in a road accident after being hit by a Ford Endeavour in Gurgaon. The incident occurred while she was walking to her office with a colleague, who also sustained minor injuries. The driver of the car fled the scene, but the number plate was retrieved. The woman was initially admitted to a hospital in Manesar but was later transferred to Safdarjung hospital in Delhi, where she succumbed to her injuries. An FIR has been registered, and the police are currently tracing the accused. In a separate incident, a biker died after being hit by an unknown vehicle on Golf Course Road.

title: 22 dead in US mass shooting; suspect still at large
Amritpal Singh’s father stopped from flying out
'Ghostbusters' in Hyd give residents sleepless nights
description: The Kundanbagh colony in Hyderabad has been disturbed by a group of young men on motorbikes who believe a house in the area is haunted. This frenzy has been caused by videos posted by YouTubers, which have gained millions of views. The locals are frustrated and have captured CCTV footage of the late-night chaos. The police have intervened and arrested 35 youngsters for creating a nuisance. This is not the first time such an incident has occurred, and the locals believe that all digital impressions of the house need to be removed to prevent recurring incidents.

title: Google has new rules for Android apps: How they will help users
description: Google has announced new developer policies for Android apps that use generative AI technology. Developers will be required to include a way for users to report offensive AI-generated content within the app. The aim is to ensure that AI-generated content is safe and that user feedback is incorporated. In addition, apps using AI must prevent the generation of restricted content.

title: What is Google's pain and Microsoft's 'big gain'
description: Microsoft is gaining an edge over Google's parent company, Alphabet, in the cloud business. This is due to Microsoft's focus on generative artificial intelligence and big clients, while Google has concentrated on startups. Microsoft's Azure platform experienced growth in its first quarter, driven by cloud spending from enterprise clients. In contrast, Alphabet's cloud unit has seen a decline in growth due to its exposure to smaller clients. Analysts predict that AI will power growth for both companies in the long term, with Google's expected roll out of Gemini in 2023.

title: At least 22 killed in Maine mass shooting
Con who cops knew as 'VIP' given security 19 times
description: A man named Anoop Chaudhary has been arrested for posing as a Railway Board member to cheat people. However, it was discovered that Chaudhary had also pretended to be a politician, bureaucrat, and power broker to obtain VIP treatment and police security 19 times in three years. He used fake letterheads and an officer on special duty to liaise with the police and administration. Chaudhary has been involved in multiple cheating cases in different cities. The police are investigating the role of VIP cell officials in the matter.

title: Bank must compensate for cyber fraud: Consumer court
description: The Navsari Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission (CDRC) has stated that a bank is responsible for compensating customers for money lost in cyber fraud if they are promptly alerted. The CDRC ordered the State Bank of India (SBI) to pay a UPI cyber fraud victim Rs 39,578 after she personally informed the branch the same day she lost the money. The commission criticized the bank for not promptly acting and stated that it had the necessary technical capabilities to track the siphoned-off money. The bank's argument that the customer was at fault was rejected by the CDRC.
